The German version of the Finder of Paths Unseen spirit promo for Spirit Island. Pegasus Spiele released the spirits from Spirit Island: Promo Pack 2 seperately.

&bdquo;Finder unsichtbarer Wege ist den Dahan wohlbekannt: Er durchquert m&uuml;helos die Insel und die meisten Geister-Redner haben ihn schon getroffen. Er kommuniziert direkter als andere Geister, indem er seine hohen Triller mit Ebenen von Gedanken &uuml;berlagert. Manchmal hilft er Seelen gestorbener Dahan auf ihrem Weg, bevor b&ouml;sartige Geister sie verschlingen k&ouml;nnen. Obwohl er allgegenw&auml;rtig ist, bleibt er r&auml;tselhaft. Sogar die Dahan, die ihn den Wegbereiter nennen, sind sich nicht sicher, ob er wirklich neue Wege erschafft oder findet, was bereits da ist. Ist die Parallelwelt, durch die er sich bewegt, &uuml;berhaupt r&auml;umlich oder eine andere Daseinsform? Die Gedanken, die er kommuniziert, sind so fremdartig, dass sie sich nur schwer in Worte fassen lassen.

Finder unsichtbarer Wege ist ein zus&auml;tzlicher Geist f&uuml;r Spirit Island mit sehr hoher Komplexit&auml;t Dieser Geist bewegt die meiste Zeit Invasoren und manchmal Dahan, Pr&auml;senzen oder Tiere. Dadurch (und durch reichlich Isolieren) kann er gut invasorenfreie, &bdquo;sichere&ldquo; Zonen schaffen. Ohne eine M&ouml;glichkeit vernichtete Pr&auml;senzen zur&uuml;ck ins Spiel zu bringen, kann er es sich nur selten leisten, Invasoren zu zerst&ouml;ren. Daher ben&ouml;tigt er eine passende Starke F&auml;higkeit &ndash; oder Mitspieler, die ihn bei Angriffen unterst&uuml;tzen. Da er die Topologie der Insel &auml;ndert, steigert sich die Komplexit&auml;t f&uuml;r alle Spieler &ndash; vor allem in gr&ouml;&szlig;eren Spielen!&ldquo;

Objective
All players play on the same team against a ghost that haunts the coded castle. Their task is to play the role of a wise sorcerer defending the fortress and collect four treasures before the ghost reaches the top of the castle tower.

How to play?
Although you all play on the sorcerer&rsquo;s team, each player makes their own moves each turn. Of course, this does not mean that you cannot consult other players &ndash; many sorcerers are better than one! Each turn starts with drawing three cards in a pile and putting them in a row. The youngest sorcerer on the team starts their turn and then performs the moves indicated by the cards in order (left to right). After the moves are completed, the used cards are put aside and the next three cards are drawn and put in a row by the next player. You can also play alone and go on a creative and exciting adventure when there are no other board game lovers nearby!

You can draw:

     arrow cards: move the sorcerer to an adjacent field on the board, in the direction indicated by the arrow. NOTE: in each turn, you can rotate up to two of these cards by 90&deg; in any direction, or you can leave them as they were lined up;
     loop cards: repeat the movements indicated by the cards to the left of this card twice, one by one, if this card is placed first from the left, it remains inactive;
     sorcerer cards: move to any of adjacent fields on the left, right, above or below;
     ghost cards: move the ghost token one field up.


There are special fields on the board, which may make it easier (or more difficult) for you to collect treasures:

     if you enter a teleportation gate field, you can magically move the sorcerer to any other gate field;
     if you enter or pass through a field with a sorcerer&rsquo;s wand, you 


 can move the ghost token one field down;

     you cannot stop or pass through the ghost fields; turn the arrows to walk around them.


When you enter the treasure field, put it in one of the boxes at the top of the board. If you use all the cards before the end of the game, shuffle them carefully and stack them again (since there are 35 cards, only two cards are dealt in the last turn). If the sequence you draw makes movement impossible (for example: even after turning the cards you hit a ghost field or you can&rsquo;t walk because of the end of the route), you move the ghost token one field up. You will win if you collect all the treasures before the ghost moves to the last field of its route and leaves the castle tower.

&mdash;description from the rulebook

Hardcoded is a simultaneous action-selection fighting game, where players secretly program their characters to perform special moves in an attempt to outmaneuver and ultimately knock out their opponents. The game can be played free-for-all (2, 3, or 4 players), in teams of 2 (4 players), or against an AI opponent.

The game is played in rounds. Each round consists of several parts:
1. roll for speed (simultaneous, secret);
2. select actions (simultaneous, secret);
3. reveal actions;
4. player turns (each player in speed order move on the board and attack if possible);
5. pass priority tracker and start the next round.

Each character starts with 5 HP. When a character is dealt damage, their HP is reduced by that amount. A character reduced to 0 HP is Knocked Out (KO&rsquo;d). A KO&rsquo;d character respawns at the end of the current round. The player that KO&rsquo;d them receives 1 point, and the first player (or team) to reach 2 points wins.

A solitaire game of stacking, sliding & swapping Looney Labs pyramids to match up monochrome trees. Create all 15 trees to win!

&lsquo;So you&rsquo;re ready to fly in my forces?&rsquo; the Emperor said, sliding a scrambled Solomids setup across the table.  &rsquo;First, you must prove your pyramidian prowess.  Win without swapping and you shall command an entire cavalry!  A one-swap victory, and you&rsquo;ll captain your own ship; swap two and it&rsquo;s off to cadet school for you! But lose&hellip;&lsquo;

Using a flat playing surface, and a Looney Labs pyramid set composed of 9 pyramids (3 smalls, 3 mediums, & 3 large) each of 5 different colors, totaling 45 pieces; win the game by assembling one small-medium-large stack of the same color (called a tree or tree-trio) at a time, attempting to form three complete &lsquo;rainbow stashes&rsquo; (five tree-trios, one of every color).

Three additional quest cards: The Gates of Galvoie, Broceliande and The White Lance are available from the publisher as a Print On Demand expansion for the base game.

